<subSubSection id="AB632E7CBFC6AE439D306210375A7B68" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="6EFCB393BE18149BD6CF9D7DC4F308F3" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BE734BB7F24F5DC398764A79C1AB638C" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">
This is a common genus of grass-living species in tropical and subtropical areas (
<bibRefCitation id="DCC26AEC399C0E48990DABFADF01EB05" author="Mound, LA" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs on Entomology, International" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 487" title="The Thrips of central and south America: An introduction (Insecta: Thysanoptera)." volume="6" year="1996">Mound and Marullo 1996</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="80C8A6DD3FAD51FE0F379847C9DB61BC" author="Mound, LA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 40" title="Grass-dependent Thysanoptera of the family Thripidae from Australia." volume="3064" year="2011 a">Mound 2011a</bibRefCitation>
), with nine species worldwide (
<bibRefCitation id="1DCDA0432923A4E9C8173C240CDA01E2" author="Mound, LA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 40" title="Grass-dependent Thysanoptera of the family Thripidae from Australia." volume="3064" year="2011 a">Mound 2011a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="95B74F1B0EFEB82DAA3F47546E22BD5E" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">ThripsWiki 2013</bibRefCitation>
) of these 
<taxonomicName id="29F70EB16FFFC01B19D57F758D94753D" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Bregmatothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bregmatothrips bournieri" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bournieri">Bregmatothrips bournieri</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="7DD3A3A90E20A6550F4C0518A18B2A3C" originalValue="Pelikán">Pelikan</normalizedToken>
is found in Iran (
<bibRefCitation id="C02F0689FCFF984CF2F4F626C87E35C0" author="Pelikan, J" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" pagination="464 - 468" title="A new Irano-Turkmenian species of Bregmatothrips Hood, 1912." volume="85" year="1988">
<normalizedToken id="42F8706D94B69EC61072CF9D95D51879" originalValue="Pelikán">Pelikan</normalizedToken>
1988
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="CF7DCD0A65366AD80F305F86A7BEC3EF" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Bhatti et al. 2009a</bibRefCitation>
). This genus is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="8B8B610C077BC7958B61460A5D5A09D4" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Sorghothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sorghothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sorghothrips</taxonomicName>
by having antennal segment I with paired median dorsoapical setae, and the abdominal tergites with posteromarginal craspeda and the median campaniform sensilla close to the posterior margin (
<bibRefCitation id="2249D735AD725877429618A0168C2E33" author="Masumoto, M" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 90" title="A revision of and key to the world species of Mycterothrips Trybom (Thysanoptera, Thripidae)." volume="1261" year="2006">Masumoto and Okajima 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
